Two persons kidnapped by Boko Haram insurgents in Borno State have regained their freedom. DAILY POST recalls that the President, Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Samson Supo Ayokunle sometime in July called on President Muhammadu Buhari to ensure the release of Miss Leah Sharibu, Moses Oyeleke and Grace Taku and other hostages in the den of the Boko Haram terrorists. One of the persons released is a pastor with Living Faith Church, Moses Oyeleke, who was abducted sometime in April. The other person, Ndagilaya Umar, is a female teacher at Government Science Secondary School, Askira, TVC reports. Their release was secured through the efforts of Governor Babagana Zulum and two Non-Governmental Organisations. The army and the Department of State Services were also involved in providing logistics and intelligence for their release. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.